LAGOS – Determined to take the mining sector to the desired level, the Minister of Mines and Steel Development, Olamilekan Adegbite, has called for cooperation among the Federal and state governments, as well as the three arms of government. Adegbite noted this while responding to journalists’ questions after a meeting with Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu at the State House, Marina, Lagos, on Thursday. The minister led other members of the committee on Mines and Steel set up by the National Executive (NEC) in its last meeting to look into grey areas in the new push by the Federal Government to increase the tempo of activities in the mining sector, with Ekiti State Governor Kayode Fayemi, as the committee’s chairman. The minister said that mining activities can be debilitating in some cases, putting a lot of toll on the infrastructure of the states.